<TITLE> BSF frees abducted farmer </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, Apr 30 (bdnews24.com) Indian Border Security Force have freed the Bangladeshi farmer seven hours into his abduction from Shingnagar border of Chapainawabganj, BDR officials said on Friday. Shakib Mia, 45, son of Zamidar Mia of Monakasha union at Shibganj upazila was whisked away while he was working in the fields, BDR officials said. Major Nazrul Islam, operation officer of Chapainawabganj 39 Rifles Battalion, said, 151 BSF Battalion's soldiers of Daulatpur camp in India crossed the border and entered about 100 meters into Bangladesh at around 9.30am and abducted the farmer. Islam also said that a letter was sent by the BDR to BSF asking them to return the farmer. A flag meeting between BDR and BSF was held along the Shingnagar border at around 4.30pm where Shakib was returned. bd
